Market Analysis and Size

The global automatic dependent surveillance-broadcast market is fragmented in nature as it consists of many major players such as Collins Aerospace, Sagetech Avionics, Inc., Avidyne Corporation, and uAvionix. The presence of these companies covers a major portion of new product launches in the market. These players offer automatic dependent surveillance-broadcast products from single customers to mega businesses with various products and technical support. Some of the factors such as the advancement in cloud technologies, rapid R&D in surveillance-broadcast services, and the entrance of new market players in the region are expected to boost the market growth in the future. The market is primarily driven by the advancement in ADS-B technology and increasing safety and efficiency requirements. In addition, the growing demand for airborne surveillance and unmanned aerial vehicles has fuelled the market growth. However, high installation and maintenance costs associated with ADS-B and integration challenges with existing systems are the major factors expected to restrain the market growth. Further, the increasing need for efficient airport operations and the emergence of space-based ADS-B systems provide lucrative opportunities for market growth.

